### GET SEMESTERS
## Returns a list of semesters. The result set is scoped
## to the authenticated user's role:
##   - Student -> semesters in the school
##   - Teacher -> semesters in the school
##   - Local Admin -> semesters in the school
##   - Admin -> all semesters across all schools
##
## Response Body (200 OK) - Array of semester objects, each containing:
##   - id          (UUID): Unique identifier of the semester
##   - school_id   (UUID): Unique identifier of the school
##   - name        (string): Full name of the semester (e.g. "Herbstsemester 2025")
##   - start_date  (NaiveDate): Beginning of the semester
##   - end_date    (NaiveDate): End of the semester
##
## Responses:
##   200 OK - Returns array of GetSemesterResponse objects
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
GET {{BASE}}/semester
Accept: application/json


### CREATE A SEMESTER
## Creates a new semester.
## Restricted to Local Admin or Admin roles.
##
## Request Body:
##   - name        (string, required): Full semester name (e.g. "Herbstsemester 2025")
##   - start_date  (string, required): Start date
##   - end_date    (string, required): End date
##   - school_id   (UUID, optional): UUID of the school; only necessary if a admin creates a semester
##
## Responses:
##   200 OK - Semester created successfully; returns the new semester object or its ID
##   400 Bad Request - Missing required fields or invalid UUID format
##   401 Unauthorized - Insufficient permissions for this role
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
##
# @name fs
POST {{BASE}}/semester
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json


{
    "name": "Frühlingssemester 2025",
